{meta: title Are You Walking}
{meta: artist Hank Williams}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]On your journey to the grave
[C7]Would you [F]stop and try to [C]save
Are you walking and a-talking with the [G7]Lord
Would you lend a helping [C]hand
[C7]To some [F]poor sinner [C]man
Are you walking and [G7]a-talking with the [C]Lord
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
Chorus
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
Are you walking (are you walking)
[C7]Are you talking (are you [F]talking)
Are you [C]walking and a-talking with the [G7]Lord
Are you traveling in his [C]light
[C7]Every [F]day and every [C]night
Are you walking and a talking [G7]with the [C]Lord
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
